Comment::::<div class="com_user_text">
                            Its also worth noting that NHS provides a cradle to grave service to all Britons. A high proportion of its expense comes from treating the elderly and also those whose medical conditions are self afflicted eg alcoholics and drug addicts.<br/><br/>
Any govt that wishes to follow the same model would do well to assess the most prevalent and debilitating health risks and potentially focus on those for treatment to keep its costs low. Diagnostics is one are where a lot of money is wasted. This service could be prioritized. So could accidents and emergencies. Pregnant mothers and children can be prioritized. Issues of public health like Dengue, malaria, TB, bronchial diseases can be prioritized as well<br/>
Providing generic low cost drugs is another area to focus on.<br/><br/>
Preventive health care is another area (through exercise regimen and good nutrition) where there is no clash of interests for a publically funded healthcare system.
